
Præsta, quæsumus, omnípotens Deus: ut, intercedénte beáto <sr>N.</s> Mártyre tuo, et a cunctis adversitátibus liberémur in córpore, et a pravis cogitatiónibus mundémur in mente. Per Dóminum.
Grant, we beseech thee, O almighty God, that, by the intercession of blessed <sr>N.</s> thy Martyr, our bodies may be protected from all adversity, and our hearts made pure from every evil thought. Through our Lord.
